Sentencas: A simple and mass productive extrusion technique was applied to fabricate anode-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Fabrication of Anode-Supported Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Using an Extrusion and Vacuum Infiltration Techniques

Sentencas: A standard NiO/8YSZ (nickel oxide/8 mol % yttria stabilized zirconia) cermet anode, 8YSZ electrolyte, and lanthanum strontium manganite (La0.8Sr0.2MnO3) cathode were used as the material components.
Titulo: Fabrication of Anode-Supported Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Using an Extrusion and Vacuum Infiltration Techniques

Sentencas: Secondary electron microscopy images indicated that vacuum infiltration method successfully generated the thin electrolyte layer (about 15 mu m) with a structurally effective three phase boundaries.
Titulo: Fabrication of Anode-Supported Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Using an Extrusion and Vacuum Infiltration Techniques

Sentencas: Fabricated unit cell showed the open circuit voltage of 1.12 V without any fuel leaking problems.
Titulo: Fabrication of Anode-Supported Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Using an Extrusion and Vacuum Infiltration Techniques

Sentencas: Electrochemical tests showed a maximum power density up to 0.30 W cm(-2) at 800 degrees C, implying the good performance as tubular SOFCs.
Titulo: Fabrication of Anode-Supported Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Using an Extrusion and Vacuum Infiltration Techniques

Sentencas: This study verified that the extrusion aided by vacuum infiltration process could be a promising technique for mass production of tubular SOFCs.
Titulo: Fabrication of Anode-Supported Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Using an Extrusion and Vacuum Infiltration Techniques
